<div class="main" style="background-color:rgb(46, 0, 62);">
    <!-- Main container with dark purple background -->
    <div class="title-container" style="border-color:rgb(91, 14, 14)">
        <!-- Title container with dark red border -->
        <p class="title" style="color:white;">The truth about sugar</p> <!-- Title text in white -->
    </div>
    <div class="best-text" style="background-color: rgb(245, 243, 240);border: 2px solid rgb(100, 100, 100);border-radius: 12px;">
        <!-- Content box with light background and border -->
        <p>
            Sugar isn’t just sweet — it’s strategic. It’s the most successful distraction in human history, quietly folded into every birthday party, every breakfast cereal, every "treat" given to a child before
            they can even speak.
        </p>
