            But what if it wasn’t a treat? What if it was a tranquilizer?
        </p>
        <p>
            For decades, we've been told that sugar is a reward, a comfort, a symbol of joy. But behind the frosting and sprinkles lies something darker. Sugar is engineered dependency — 
            a subtle sedative handed to the masses with a smile.
        </p>
        <p>
            The government doesn’t need chains when the people are already bound by their own desire for another bite. Sugar is the leash — and we’re trained to love the feeling of it tightening.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(70, 0, 0); font-size: 1.2vw;">
            <!-- Emphasized last paragraph -->
            This isn’t dessert. It’s a design. And the truth? The truth is bitter.
        </p>
